# writable() âœï¸

A store you can read and write to.

```javascript
// stores.js
import { writable } from 'svelte/store';
export const count = writable(0);
```
It has `set()` and `update()` methods.

# Subscribing (Hard way) ðŸ˜«

```javascript
import { count } from './stores.js';

let countValue;

const unsubscribe = count.subscribe(value => {
  countValue = value;
});

onDestroy(unsubscribe); // Prevent memory leaks!
```

# readable() ðŸ‘“

Data that the user cannot change (e.g., Mouse Position, Time, Geolocation).

```javascript
export const time = readable(new Date(), function start(set) {
  const interval = setInterval(() => set(new Date()), 1000);
  return function stop() { clearInterval(interval); };
});
```

# Custom Logic ðŸ› ï¸

A store is just an object with a `subscribe` method.

You can wrap a writable store to create domain-specific logic.

```javascript
function createCount() {
  const { subscribe, set, update } = writable(0);
  return {
    subscribe,
    increment: () => update(n => n + 1),
    reset: () => set(0)
  };
}
```
